OL,3,GStrathclyde
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA chilly but mostly sunny
OL,6,Fstart. Cloud will increase through the
OL,7,Fmorning with perhaps the odd light
OL,8,Fshower, before sunny spells develop
OL,9,Fagain later on.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FA mainly dry evening with
OL,12,Fsome late sunny spells. Patchy cloud
OL,13,Fthrough the night may give the odd
OL,14,Fspot of rain, but most places will
OL,15,Fremain dry.
OL,16,
OL,17,CWednesday:FA largely cloudy start to
OL,18,Fthe day with a few spots of rain for
OL,19,FArgyll. Otherwise a dry and bright day
OL,20,Fwith a few hazy sunny spells.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
